interlotting
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:[wool sales] a grouping of small lines of wool from different farmers into one sale lot.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
