Citations
Date: 0/0/1919
Source: Wool in NZ
Author:
Vol / Page: 32
Edition:
Quote: At the present time much interlotting is done. ie the grouping together of different farmers' small lines of wool of as near the one quality as possible.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/2001
Source: Woolpro Glossary of Wool Terms
Author: WOOLPRO
Vol / Page: 18
Edition:
Quote: Interlotting or Grouping: The process in a broker's store of selling together complete bales of wool of the same class but belonging to several different owners to form a larger saleable line.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1982
Source: MAF Agricultural Glossary
Author: MAF
Vol / Page: 56
Edition:
Quote: Interlotting: Method of preparation of wool for sale by a wool broker whereby one to three straight bales of a type from one grower are matched with other growers' bales of a smilar type to make a saleable line.
Notes:
